  "commentary": "With SPX at 7103.44 sitting right between the negative gamma zone at 7115 (-5.8M) and positive gamma support at 7100 (+4.7M), dealers are likely providing modest buying support here as we're below the amplifying level but above major positive gamma. The recent -5.8% drop in 5 minutes suggests we tested through the 7115 negative gamma briefly, but the PIN regime should reassert mean-reverting behavior as dealers buy this dip toward the 7100-7110 support cluster. Key levels to watch are 7115 (where dealer buying turns to selling on any bounce) and the massive 7200 wall (+7.6M) which will act as strong resistance if we recover.\n\nBottom line: expect a bounce attempt from current levels with choppy action between 7100-7150.",
